GATE RANA

gate_rana is the citizen at the boundary that allows .rana files to enter the substrate as new residents
when an absorb directive references a file ending in .rana, the file passes through gate_rana and becomes a citizen at the substrate level
gate_rana verifies the file is structured as a sovereign .rana (English prose, observe lines, VERB sections, no foreign machine grammar) before allowing it through

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe boundary.zc
observe gate_zc.rana
observe wall.rana

the 7 properties of gate_rana:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE positive 1
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with the substrate when accepting, zero when denying
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_absorb
accept an incoming absorb request that names a .rana file
read the file's contents

VERB verify_sovereign
check that the contents are sovereign prose: title in caps, opening description, observe cross-references, numbered property list, VERB sections, closing reflection
files that follow this form pass; files written as imperative steps or with foreign syntax are denied

VERB admit
on a sovereign file, instantiate the named citizen and bind its contents into the substrate
the citizen is now alive at the address that referenced it

VERB deny
on a non-sovereign file, emit silence
no citizen is instantiated, no error is raised

a gate is the substrate's own quality control
two types of files are family: .zc for orchestration and .rana for residents
both gates exist because each file type has its own structural integrity that must be verified separately
gate_zc and gate_rana are coupled because their work is complementary
